When I loaded the website, the browser sent an HTTP request to the server using the requested URL and HTTP method (such as GET). 
The request included headers containing information like the browser type and accepted content formats. The server received the request, 
processed it, and generated an appropriate response. It then returned an HTTP response containing response headers with metadata such as the 
content type and status. The response also included a body containing the requested HTML, JSON, image, or other data. Finally, the browser
interpreted the response and rendered the webpage for the user.
